::Q01_Playwright_Test_Runner::
What does the Playwright Test Runner provide besides executing tests? {
=Built-in test discovery, parallelism, fixtures, reporting, and retries
~Only a thin wrapper over browser automation
~A replacement for Node.js runtime
~A CI/CD pipeline tool
}

::Q02_Runs_Playwright_Tests::
Which command runs Playwright tests in headed mode? {
=npx playwright test --headed
~npx playwright run --ui
~npx playwright headed
~npx playwright test --show
}

::Q03_Purpose_test.describe::
What is the purpose of test.describe()? {
=To group related tests into logical sections
~To declare global setup logic
~To disable parallel execution
~To create a new Playwright project
}

::Q04_Before_Individual_Test::
Which hook runs before every individual test? {
=test.beforeEach
~test.beforeAll
~test.afterAll
~test.afterEach
}

::Q05_test.only()::
What does test.only() do? {
=Runs only that test and ignores others in the file
~Skips the test
~Retries the test until it passes
~Marks the test as expected to fail
}

::Q06_Auto-waits_Condition::
Which assertion auto-waits until the condition is met? {
=expect(locator).toBeVisible()
~expect(value).toBe(5)
~expect.soft(value).toMatch(/x/)
~expect(page).toMatchSnapshot()
}

::Q07_expect.soft()::
What does expect.soft() allow? {
=Collecting multiple assertion failures without stopping the test
~Retrying the whole test automatically
~Running assertions in parallel
~Skipping assertions based on browser
}

::Q08_Controls_Parallel::
Which config option controls the number of parallel workers? {
=workers
~retries
~timeout
~expect.timeout
}

::Q09_FullyParallel::
What does fullyParallel: true enable? {
=All tests run in parallel, even within the same file
~Each file runs serially by default
~Only browsers run in parallel, not tests
~Parallel screenshots during execution
}

::Q10_Browser/Device_Settings?::
Which configuration section controls browser/device settings? {
=use
~projects
~reporter
~hooks
}

::Q11_Playwright_Config::
What is the purpose of projects in Playwright config? {
=To run tests across multiple browsers or environments
~To define global hooks
~To organize files on disk
~To automatically generate documentation
}

::Q12_StorageState::
What does storageState allow? {
=Reusing authenticated browser session state across tests
~Saving video and trace artifacts
~Controlling where screenshots are stored
~Injecting environment variables
}

::Q13_test.describe.serial()::
What does test.describe.serial() enforce? {
=Tests inside run sequentially, not in parallel
~Tests inside run multiple times
~Tests inside are skipped
~Tests inside cannot contain hooks
}

::Q14_Retries_in_Config::
What does retries in config define? {
=How many times to retry a failing test
~Maximum number of parallel workers
~Number of browser contexts per worker
~How many assertions can fail softly
}

::Q15_test.skip()::
What does test.skip() do? {
=Marks the test as skipped and prevents execution
~Runs the test only in specific environments
~Causes the test to retry indefinitely
~Marks the test as critical
}

::Q16_HTTP_API_testing::
Which fixture provides the HTTP API testing context? {
=request
~page
~context
~browser
}

::Q17_testInfo.retry::
What does testInfo.retry indicate? {
=Current retry attempt index (0-based)
~Total number of retries allowed
~Milliseconds spent waiting for assertions
~Whether the test is soft-failed
}

::Q18_Setup_Project::
What is the purpose of a setup project? {
=To run authentication or DB seeding before other projects
~To speed up browser launch
~To disable default fixtures
~To collect coverage reports
}

::Q19_ignoreHTTPSErrors::
What does ignoreHTTPSErrors: true do? {
=Allows navigating to HTTPS sites with invalid certificates
~Ignores failed API responses
~Skips all failing SSL tests
~Prevents browser redirects
}

::Q20_Trace::
What does trace: 'on-first-retry' enable? {
=Trace recording only on the first retry of a failing test
~Tracing every test execution
~Tracing only test.describe blocks
~Tracing disabled globally
}

